Phenotypic a bit confusing at first. Typical A. obscura dull green body, but with glossy black bill, not bicolored. It's pair showed up eventually (female) and it had the more typical paler lower mandible and brown upper mandible. Update: Recorded a male M. bicolor near Neiva, Huila with the exact same song. That bird had the same color bill as this bird. I think this was a subadult male M. bicolor with a female. 

Track 1 - natural song
Track 2 - song in response to playback of Track 1
Track 3 - calls of pair in response to playback of self
